<TITLE> CHT Land Commission to be revived </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  The government will revive the CHT Land Commission to implement the peace agreement, the law minister said on Tuesday. "The government will revive the Land Commission on Chittagong Hill Tracts in implementing the peace accord. A retired judge might be given the charge of the commission," Shafiq Ahmed told reporters. "The Awami League government closed the peace agreement. The same government will do everything possible for the implementation of the accord," he said after a meeting with a delegation of international commission on CHT affairs. On whether any old law would be reformed, the minister said: "If necessary the old laws might be changed." Lord Eric Avebury led the eight-member delegation that included Sarah Hossain, Swapan Adnan, Meghna Guha Thakurata, Christina Nelson and Shirin Sultana. b
